          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1699364026647-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> creamy cashew paste </strong>and <strong>remaining soaking liquid </strong>to the pan with your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and the <strong>chicken tikka</strong> (and any juices from the tray)</p><p>Turn the heat up to high and cook for 7-8 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>creamy free range chicken makhani</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1699364033149-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
